  "prompt": "3 digit no unit digit, ten digit and hundred digit their ratio 3:5:7 if the difference of original number and \u0155eversing the digit is 396 find the no?",
  "response": "Let's solve this step by step:\n\n1) Let's represent the digits:\n   \u2022 Unit digit = x\n   \u2022 Ten digit = y\n   \u2022 Hundred digit = z\n\n2) According to the ratio condition:\n   x : y : z = 3 : 5 : 7\n\n3) Let's assume x = 3k, y = 5k, z = 7k\n   Where k is a constant\n\n4) The original number will be: 100z + 10y + x\n   = 100(7k) + 10(5k) + 3k\n   = 700k + 50k + 3k\n   = 753k\n\n5) The reversed number will be: 100x + 10y + z\n   = 100(3k) + 10(5k) + 7k\n   = 300k + 50k + 7k\n   = 357k\n\n6) Given condition: Original number - Reversed number = 396\n   753k - 357k = 396\n   396k = 396\n   k = 1\n\n7) Substituting k = 1:\n   \u2022 Unit digit (x) = 3\n   \u2022 Ten digit (y) = 5\n   \u2022 Hundred digit (z) = 7\n\n8) The number is: 753\n\n9) Let's verify:\n   Original number = 753\n   Reversed number = 357\n   753 - 357 = 396 \u2713\n\nThe number is 753.",
